WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.000
These are...

00:00:10.439 --> 00:00:12.120
But how did they get here?

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:38.420
It doesn't make sense.

00:00:46.420 --> 00:00:47.340
That's...

00:00:47.340 --> 00:00:47.980
impossible.

00:00:48.920 --> 00:00:49.859
Isn't it?

00:00:50.379 --> 00:00:51.600
How did he get in here?

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:07.400
Mr. Song, this means they had to shut the broadcast down for something, right?

00:01:08.439 --> 00:01:09.000
Hmm.

00:01:09.719 --> 00:01:10.799
But why?

00:01:11.420 --> 00:01:12.760
What's happening over there?

00:01:15.859 --> 00:01:16.920
It's no good.

00:01:17.340 --> 00:01:18.780
Too much confusion at the scene.

00:01:19.359 --> 00:01:21.760
There must be a way to confirm their status.

00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:23.879
Gather all the intel we can.

00:01:24.400 --> 00:01:24.859
Yes, sir.

00:01:27.039 --> 00:01:27.599
Director!

00:01:28.079 --> 00:01:29.980
So many viewers are calling in at once.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:31.640
It's crashing the phone system.

00:01:31.819 --> 00:01:33.980
They're demanding we resume the broadcast.

00:01:34.180 --> 00:01:35.719
And we would if we could!

00:01:36.180 --> 00:01:37.620
But in case you haven't noticed,

00:01:37.840 --> 00:01:39.680
we lost contact, so there's nothing to show!

00:01:40.900 --> 00:01:41.379
Besides,

00:01:41.700 --> 00:01:43.980
what do we do if all the S-Ranks are already dead?

00:01:47.319 --> 00:01:48.900
Hey, what's going on?

00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:50.460
We need an update right now!

00:01:51.340 --> 00:01:51.939
Are you...

00:01:51.939 --> 00:01:53.079
Damn it!

00:01:53.379 --> 00:01:54.640
My camera quit working.

00:01:55.219 --> 00:01:56.260
Of all the times.

00:01:57.460 --> 00:01:57.859
Iron.

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:00.239
Iron.

00:02:06.620 --> 00:02:07.239
Go.

00:02:18.900 --> 00:02:20.920
I'm not following any of this.

00:02:21.680 --> 00:02:22.699
Who are these shadows?

00:02:23.819 --> 00:02:26.800
And how did Hunter's son even get to the island?

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:31.000
Oh, there you are.

00:02:31.319 --> 00:02:32.319
And just in time.

00:02:32.819 --> 00:02:34.419
But how the hell did you...

00:02:34.419 --> 00:02:35.560
I can explain it later.

00:02:36.379 --> 00:02:38.219
Let's take care of your wounds in the meantime.

00:02:39.039 --> 00:02:39.939
Here, this should help.

00:02:41.879 --> 00:02:42.360
Right.

00:02:42.800 --> 00:02:44.620
The system won't let me hand these off.

00:02:46.039 --> 00:02:47.199
You summoned that?

00:02:47.520 --> 00:02:48.920
Your magic sure is handy.

00:02:49.479 --> 00:02:50.000
Hunter Ma.

00:02:51.740 --> 00:02:53.460
I need you to open your mouth.

00:02:58.420 --> 00:02:59.460
That's unreal.

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.860
I'm healed.

00:03:05.759 --> 00:03:06.319
Completely.

00:03:14.900 --> 00:03:16.479
She's still in bad shape.

00:03:16.960 --> 00:03:18.219
Why isn't it working?

00:03:19.659 --> 00:03:21.319
Damn, it's just like before.

00:03:21.759 --> 00:03:23.780
These can't work when your health is too low.

00:03:24.520 --> 00:03:26.099
And her aura is getting weaker.

00:03:27.539 --> 00:03:29.620
Her wounds are too severe for potions to heal.

00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:31.280
We have to leave now.

00:03:31.500 --> 00:03:33.060
I can clear a path for us.

00:03:33.240 --> 00:03:33.680
All right.

00:03:33.780 --> 00:03:34.280
Hold on.

00:03:39.620 --> 00:03:42.000
They certainly swarm like the bugs they are.

00:03:42.259 --> 00:03:44.120
How are we going to take down so many of them?

00:03:48.460 --> 00:03:49.240
Chairman, go.

00:03:49.879 --> 00:03:51.520
Any news on the strike team?

00:03:51.759 --> 00:03:52.479
No, not yet.

00:03:52.939 --> 00:03:55.000
Something's jamming all comms from the island,

00:03:55.099 --> 00:03:56.319
but hopefully it's only temporary.

00:03:56.319 --> 00:03:59.219
We can't get through to Japanese command either.

00:03:59.500 --> 00:03:59.879
Not sure what...

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:00.500
Why?

00:04:00.939 --> 00:04:02.939
Touched base with the civilian media, though,

00:04:02.939 --> 00:04:04.939
and the last thing they saw was the Black Ant.

00:04:05.819 --> 00:04:07.819
It's imperative we get that signal back.

00:04:08.740 --> 00:04:11.620
And I want those medic and retrieval teams ready to move out.

00:04:12.020 --> 00:04:12.620
Yes, sir.

00:04:16.819 --> 00:04:17.819
You know, Jincho,

00:04:18.620 --> 00:04:22.500
this has to be the most I've ever resented this aging body of mine.

00:04:24.240 --> 00:04:26.040
Even if I'd be of no help to them,

00:04:26.379 --> 00:04:28.000
I wish I could join the fight.

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:29.660
I'm not sure I'll be able to do that alone.

00:04:29.660 --> 00:04:30.120
Chairman, go.

00:04:30.939 --> 00:04:34.300
Instead, all I can do is pray.

00:04:38.459 --> 00:04:39.819
Stupid technology!

00:04:40.639 --> 00:04:41.720
First the feed cuts,

00:04:41.839 --> 00:04:44.839
then the whole dang TV decides this is the perfect time to break.

00:04:45.120 --> 00:04:46.060
We're jinxed.

00:04:46.259 --> 00:04:48.079
Well, beating it up won't fix it, honey.

00:04:49.100 --> 00:04:49.579
Whatever.

00:04:50.220 --> 00:04:51.279
I'll watch it in my room.

00:04:52.279 --> 00:04:53.759
Bet my phone will have updates.

00:04:53.759 --> 00:04:54.759
Maybe.

00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:00.000
That girl is so restless.

00:05:01.819 --> 00:05:03.819
I want answers, so explain.

00:05:04.500 --> 00:05:06.500
Goto-san's vital signs went silent, sir.

00:05:08.339 --> 00:05:10.339
Right before the signal was cut,

00:05:10.800 --> 00:05:12.800
he was confronted by a powerful enemy,

00:05:12.800 --> 00:05:14.800
and likely killed.

00:05:15.800 --> 00:05:16.800
And the others?

00:05:16.800 --> 00:05:18.800
We haven't verified.

00:05:18.800 --> 00:05:19.800
Well, figure it out.

00:05:20.500 --> 00:05:23.500
Any further losses will cost us in the next phase.

00:05:24.800 --> 00:05:25.300
On it.

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:30.420
Is someone under her control?

00:05:30.819 --> 00:05:31.879
Just watch and see.

00:05:32.120 --> 00:05:33.220
Goto got himself killed!

00:05:38.139 --> 00:05:39.240
Useless moron.

00:05:40.339 --> 00:05:42.040
What in the hell is happening on that island?

00:05:44.060 --> 00:05:46.120
Sir mientras subs

00:05:55.899 --> 00:05:57.100
Elites like Igris and Iron

00:05:57.100 --> 00:05:57.860
are holding their own,

00:05:57.860 --> 00:05:59.240
that I didn't have an audience.

00:06:01.400 --> 00:06:02.280
New plan.

00:06:03.020 --> 00:06:04.780
We're not making any progress.

00:06:05.180 --> 00:06:07.120
Time to try a more aggressive strategy.

00:06:07.960 --> 00:06:08.740
See that mage?

00:06:10.100 --> 00:06:12.259
You all hang back and stay behind him.

00:06:12.980 --> 00:06:15.199
My other shadows will deal with the ant problem.

00:06:16.220 --> 00:06:18.600
If any of them do get past my soldiers,

00:06:19.199 --> 00:06:20.400
make them regret it.

00:06:20.879 --> 00:06:21.660
Easy enough.

00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:23.699
We can handle a plan like that.

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:24.520
For sure.

00:06:25.220 --> 00:06:26.040
One last thing.

00:06:26.040 --> 00:06:28.939
Please keep what you're about to see to yourselves.

00:06:31.140 --> 00:06:34.640
Is he...

00:06:34.640 --> 00:06:55.920
It came back already?

00:06:56.040 --> 00:06:58.180
I thought it went after Gotoh.

00:06:59.020 --> 00:07:00.280
Does that mean he lost?

00:07:18.240 --> 00:07:21.000
There was no king outside.

00:07:21.939 --> 00:07:23.140
Is he in here?

00:07:24.140 --> 00:07:26.020
The one you call?

00:07:26.040 --> 00:07:26.540
King.

00:07:28.340 --> 00:07:31.220
I can't sense the shadow I sent with Gotoh.

00:07:31.760 --> 00:07:32.920
Now I know why.

00:07:34.580 --> 00:07:35.220
Wait!

00:07:35.220 --> 00:07:35.280
Wait!

00:07:35.279 --> 00:07:43.339
.

00:07:43.339 --> 00:07:49.259
Here it goes.

00:07:55.379 --> 00:07:56.619
Is it you?

00:07:57.839 --> 00:08:00.299
Are you the king of humans?

00:08:02.459 --> 00:08:03.000
Cute.

00:08:04.019 --> 00:08:05.259
They got bugs that get me.

00:08:05.279 --> 00:08:07.279
Can you even talk now?

00:08:07.279 --> 00:08:09.279
Human.

00:08:11.279 --> 00:08:13.279
Quite the remarkable aura.

00:08:20.279 --> 00:08:23.279
Okay, but you're still just a bug.

00:08:23.279 --> 00:08:25.279
This might be too much even for him.

00:08:25.279 --> 00:08:27.279
I guess we're about to see.

00:08:27.279 --> 00:08:35.279
Director, the feed is up again!

00:08:35.279 --> 00:08:37.279
Isn't he the...

00:08:37.279 --> 00:08:40.279
It doesn't matter. Let's just air it.

00:08:40.279 --> 00:08:44.279
Sir! You realize we'll be broadcasting without any delay.

00:08:44.279 --> 00:08:47.279
If something happens live, we've no way to stop it getting out.

00:08:47.279 --> 00:08:51.279
We've already cut the broadcast once. Can't get any worse than that. Do it!

00:08:51.279 --> 00:08:53.279
Yes, right!

00:08:53.279 --> 00:08:57.279
Our future, the battle, everything!

00:08:57.279 --> 00:09:00.279
Is riding on this man.

00:09:00.279 --> 00:09:02.279
I can't believe it.

00:09:02.279 --> 00:09:04.279
Me neither.

00:09:04.279 --> 00:09:06.279
He's really there.

00:09:11.279 --> 00:09:14.279
No... way...

00:09:15.279 --> 00:09:16.279
Jinu?!

00:09:16.279 --> 00:09:20.279
He said he was just stepping out! What the heck?!

00:09:20.279 --> 00:09:22.279
He better break this habit!

00:09:24.279 --> 00:09:27.279
He made it there! Thank you, Hunter-san!

00:09:28.279 --> 00:09:31.279
It's him, all right. But how do you reach them?

00:09:31.279 --> 00:09:36.279
Point is, he did it. I don't care how. Let's put our faith in him.

00:09:49.279 --> 00:09:51.279
Why would a mage-type get that close to it?!

00:09:51.279 --> 00:09:56.279
He underestimated that ant's power. And got clobbered for it.

00:09:57.279 --> 00:10:00.279
Wreak... You are no king.

00:10:24.279 --> 00:10:26.279
Um... hey... guys?

00:10:27.279 --> 00:10:29.279
Are you sure that Hunter-san is a mage?

00:10:29.279 --> 00:10:32.279
I'm not sure about anything when it comes to him.

00:10:32.279 --> 00:10:35.279
And I definitely didn't expect this.

00:10:36.279 --> 00:10:39.279
He's pretty durable. The exoskeleton, maybe.

00:10:42.279 --> 00:10:45.279
The Exoskeleton

00:10:45.279 --> 00:10:48.279
The Exoskeleton

00:10:48.279 --> 00:10:51.279
The Exoskeleton

00:10:51.279 --> 00:10:54.279
The Exoskeleton

00:10:54.279 --> 00:10:57.279
The Exoskeleton

00:10:57.279 --> 00:11:02.279
The Exoskeleton

00:11:03.279 --> 00:11:19.079
долю

00:11:19.080 --> 00:11:27.879
How?

00:11:29.639 --> 00:11:31.860
I do not understand.

00:11:32.420 --> 00:11:35.280
How could a human be so strong?

00:11:49.080 --> 00:12:02.100
Poison.

00:12:03.000 --> 00:12:07.220
A mixture of toxins from the marine life here.

00:12:07.220 --> 00:12:11.300
Its potency amplified by my magic power.

00:12:13.759 --> 00:12:17.400
You will lose all ability to move before long.

00:12:19.080 --> 00:12:20.920
This is the end for you.

00:12:21.700 --> 00:12:22.500
Die, you!

00:12:27.080 --> 00:12:29.620
Seven KIA in a ten-man team?

00:12:30.080 --> 00:12:30.900
Is that a joke?

00:12:31.500 --> 00:12:32.960
No, it's the fact.

00:12:33.639 --> 00:12:37.000
We were able to contact the three survivors, and they confirmed it.

00:12:39.259 --> 00:12:41.300
We lost over half our hunters?

00:12:41.600 --> 00:12:43.020
This mission is a catastrophe!

00:12:44.200 --> 00:12:48.440
Oh, and we've also detected a strong reading near the island's caldera.

00:12:49.080 --> 00:12:51.320
We think it's whatever beat Goto-san, sir.

00:12:51.800 --> 00:12:53.940
How is it alive after fighting him?

00:12:54.320 --> 00:12:55.840
And it's headed into the nest?

00:12:56.160 --> 00:12:56.639
Why?

00:12:56.900 --> 00:12:57.740
No idea.

00:12:58.440 --> 00:12:59.720
It could have some objective.

00:13:00.600 --> 00:13:02.600
Or maybe it needs a safe place to heal.

00:13:04.440 --> 00:13:07.100
We don't know if the Korean team is alive.

00:13:07.840 --> 00:13:11.520
But if they are hanging on by a thread, Goto's killer will cut it.

00:13:12.120 --> 00:13:16.480
They'll fall easily in their state, and the ants will be worn out from fighting, too.

00:13:17.460 --> 00:13:19.060
If we can strike down the storm...

00:13:19.340 --> 00:13:21.639
...the others will just be fodder.

00:13:22.400 --> 00:13:25.320
Victory is not lost!

00:13:26.000 --> 00:13:28.480
Hurry up and recover the three surviving S-Ranks!

00:13:29.500 --> 00:13:33.120
Once they've joined the second strike team at sea, send them back to the island!

00:13:34.540 --> 00:13:37.660
Those are your orders. A chopper will be there soon.

00:13:39.040 --> 00:13:39.720
Roger that.

00:13:41.920 --> 00:13:44.820
He wants to move ahead with Plan 9. Let's go.

00:13:45.720 --> 00:13:46.560
It's hopeless.

00:13:46.560 --> 00:13:49.060
That thing is a monster.

00:13:49.080 --> 00:13:52.080
If we don't run, then we're history.

00:13:52.080 --> 00:13:55.840
Get a grip! No time for panic attacks!

00:13:55.840 --> 00:13:58.040
Everyone who faced that ant is dead!

00:13:58.040 --> 00:14:01.620
All S-Ranks! And you want to volunteer to be next?!

00:14:02.700 --> 00:14:04.220
You're pathetic.

00:14:04.220 --> 00:14:06.220
We don't have any choice.

00:14:06.220 --> 00:14:07.900
Deal with it.

00:14:19.080 --> 00:14:24.080
We're not going to lose.

00:14:24.080 --> 00:14:26.080
We're going to get you.

00:14:26.080 --> 00:14:28.080
We're going to get you.

00:14:28.080 --> 00:14:30.080
We're going to get you.

00:14:30.080 --> 00:14:32.080
Wait, I thought he was just poisoned.

00:14:32.080 --> 00:14:34.080
He seems okay, but is he really?

00:14:34.080 --> 00:14:38.080
At this point, nothing Hunter Sung does will surprise me.

00:14:38.080 --> 00:14:41.080
So, you had a secret weapon.

00:14:41.080 --> 00:14:45.080
I was wondering why you were holding back earlier.

00:14:45.080 --> 00:14:47.080
I was wondering why you were holding back earlier.

00:14:47.080 --> 00:14:48.080
I was wondering why you were holding back earlier.

00:14:48.080 --> 00:14:49.080
Maybe it's because of the S-Rank. Maybe it's because of the S-Rank.

00:14:49.080 --> 00:14:51.080
Maybe it's because of the S-Rank.

00:14:51.080 --> 00:14:53.080
Or, he's mutual.

00:14:53.080 --> 00:15:04.560
This is a extremely

00:15:04.560 --> 00:15:14.640
difficult task, and somehow the

00:15:14.640 --> 00:15:15.560
opec is a bit different.

00:15:15.560 --> 00:15:16.040
Or, he's just HOLLYWOOD I guess.

00:15:16.040 --> 00:15:17.240
Are you looking for an aggressive attack on me?

00:15:17.240 --> 00:15:18.220
A very personal attack, but it's a very special one.

00:15:18.220 --> 00:15:19.060
He's notelf enough to have the advantage of being more of aunchone sitter.

00:15:19.059 --> 00:15:21.059
In that case...

00:15:49.059 --> 00:15:51.059
Come at me

00:16:19.059 --> 00:16:37.299
Speed that is equal to mine.

00:16:38.739 --> 00:16:40.579
And growing even faster.

00:16:41.959 --> 00:16:43.879
How is this possible?

00:16:49.059 --> 00:16:50.500
Ehem...

